@NODE "Mail_303" " Re: redirecting STDOUT "
From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>
Date: 06-12-99 04:40:10
Subject: @{b}Re: redirecting STDOUT@{ub}

From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>

On Fri, Jun 11, 1999 at 05:12:28PM +0100, Tim Hanson wrote:
> From: Tim Hanson <msinister@connectfree.co.uk>
> 
> 
>     `cha,
>         Another quicky. I remember reading somewhere (ages ago) about
> redirecting STDOUT to a file, that you`ve opened, from within a proggy. Does
> anyone know how it`s done?

The freopen function should let you do this.  The disadvantage of
doing this is that you can never revert to the original output file.
Why not use a FILE pointer variable for your output, initialise it to
stdout, and change it to point to the new file handle later on?

-----------------------------------------------------------
