@NODE "Mail_309" " Re: Requesters "
From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>
Date: 06-27-99 17:35:45
Subject: @{b}Re: Requesters@{ub}

From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>

On Fri, Jun 25, 1999 at 04:44:41PM +0100, Mike Carter wrote:
> From: "Mike Carter" <mike.carter@bigfoot.com>
> 
> When I try to obtain alock on something that isn't really there the
> 'Please insert blahblahblah...' requester appears.  Back in Blitz
> Basic there was some fiddle to temporarly suspend the requesters.  How
> can I do this in 'C'?

Each process's pr_WindowPtr field controls such requesters.  It can be
set to -1 to disable requesters, or 0 to have them appear on the
default public screen, or to a pointer to a window on whose screen
they should appear.  So

    ((struct Process *)FindTask(0))->pr_WindowPtr = (APTR)(-1);

disables them.  You should really store the old value and restore it,
though.

> And is it legally for the future?  - even if it's not I'd like to
> know how to do it anyway :)

Yes, it's legal.

-----------------------------------------------------------
Ben Hutchings - womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk, http://www.zzumbouk.demon.co.uk
Team *AMIGA* | Jay Miner Society | Linux - the choice of a GNU generation
