@NODE "Mail_323" " Re: Shells was: Re: Q: Debugging "
From: Jesper Svennevid <jesper@fxrealm.com>
Date: 06-28-99 12:48:30
Subject: @{b}Re: Shells was: Re: Q: Debugging@{ub}

From: "Jesper Svennevid" <jesper@fxrealm.com>

> From: Voytek Laniewski <voytek@cyburban.com>
>
> Speaking of which... I replaced CON: and RAW: with their KingCON
> equivalents. What I noticed though was that I got a small but continuous
> memory leak. After doing an avail it would show that some memory
> disppeared. It did not happen if I switched back to the original shell.
> Right now I use ZShell, quite nice with name completion and all but it
> seems to have some bugs. Yes it comes with the source code but it is in
> assembly and I could not assemble it with the SAS/C's asm. So is there a
> good shell that does not have any of those problems, is small (no VincED),
> and has useful features?

Don't worry, that is NOT a bug :) KingCON is allocating memory dynamically
to buffer all the lines that you keep in history, and I think the maximum
amount of memory it allocates for one window is 64k, and it reuses the
memory when the memory-limit has been reached. (I reacted the same way at
first, but it is stated in the docs quite clearly) Try to disable the
history and you'll see that it's no longer 'losing' memory.

--
// Jesper Svennevid : jesper@fxrealm.com
   Software Developer At FXRealm Studios : http://www.fxrealm.com/


