@NODE "Mail_330" " Re: Spam? "
From: Stephen Williams <sw@nysa.u-net.com>
Date: 06-30-99 21:56:13
Subject: @{b}Re: Spam?@{ub}

From: Stephen Williams <sw@nysa.u-net.com>

Allan Odgaard wrote:
> After subscribing to this list, I've started to receive SPAM with regular
> intervals.
> Has that happend for others?

Archives of list messages are kept, and are accessible over the Web.
Your email address appears in your signature, so a "harvesting"
program scanning the Web for email addresses would have no trouble
picking it up.  Ensure that your email address is nowhere in the
text of your message and you'll minimize the risk of a "harvester"
getting hold of it.

You'll see at the top of each list message is a "From:" header,
put there by the Onelist software.  You can edit your Onelist user
profile and have it disguise your email address in the archived
messages for extra security.

I hope those suggestions are of use to you and other list members.

> And/or do any one know for a fact that 
> OneList.com actually do sell the email addresses that they obtain?

I doubt they're doing that.  They have an anti-spam policy.

-Stephen

