Subject: @{b}Still serial device troubles@{ub}

From: Jonas Hulten <bjonte@hem2.passagen.se>

I have a small program that tries to read the serial.device. The strange
thing is that after a SDCMD_QUERY and the io_Actual field is non-zero, a
CMD_READ for that amount of bytes may fail (io_Actual is zero)! This
behaviour is more frequent if I have an AGA screen as the frontmost
(normally CVPPC). Very strange.

If I use 8n1.device instead of serial.device, the machine hangs. It is
likely that the crashes and the io_Actual==0 is connected since the hanging
is also more likely to happen when the frontmost screen is and AGA one.

I have tried a lot but I can't figure out what's wrong. I will send the
sources and executable to anyone who wants to have a go at this.

/Jonas

