@NODE "Mail_342" " Re: Still serial device troubles "
From: Jonas Hulten <bjonte@hem2.passagen.se>
Date: 06-17-99 17:31:04
Subject: @{b}Re: Still serial device troubles@{ub}

From: Jonas Hulten <bjonte@hem2.passagen.se>

Den 17-Jun-99, skrev Colin Wenzel:

>> I have tried a lot but I can't figure out what's wrong. I will send the
>> sources and executable to anyone who wants to have a go at this.

> Funny you mention this right now, but a friend of mine was doing some
> "serial stuff"  the other week & had wierd things happening too...

> He didn't initialize the message replyport properly in the IOExtSer
> block...

This is my initialization:

BOOL OpenMidiIn(void)
{
  if (si = (struct SerialIn *)AllocMem(sizeof(struct SerialIn),
MEMF_PUBLIC|MEMF_CLEAR))
  {
    if (si->msgport = CreatePort(0,0))
    {
      if ( si->serialio = (struct IOExtSer *)CreateExtIO(si->msgport,
sizeof(struct IOExtSer)) )
      {
        si->serialio->io_SerFlags = SERF_SHARED;

        if ( si->deviceopen = !OpenDevice("artser.device", 0L, (struct
IORequest *)si->serialio, 0L) )
        {
          si->serialio->io_Baud = 31250;
          si->serialio->io_ReadLen = 8;
          si->serialio->io_WriteLen = 8;
          si->serialio->io_StopBits = 1;
          si->serialio->io_SerFlags = SERF_XDISABLED | SERF_RAD_BOOGIE;
          si->serialio->IOSer.io_Command = SDCMD_SETPARAMS;
          DoIO((struct IORequest *)si->serialio);
          return TRUE;
        }
      }
    }
  }

  CloseMidiIn();
  return FALSE;
}

/Jonas

