@NODE "Mail_355" " Re: Still serial device troubles "
From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>
Date: 06-24-99 02:02:02
Subject: @{b}Re: Still serial device troubles@{ub}

From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>

On Tue, Jun 22, 1999 at 11:52:37AM +1000, Colin Wenzel wrote:
<snip>
> Passing the address of an auto variable -   Oops  (:o)  !!!
> 
> you should make it STATIC or declare  it globally.....

No.  You must not use pointers to auto variables after exiting the
block in which they are defined.  This code is fine.

