@NODE "Mail_357" " Re: StormC & Hooks "
From: Yves Grabowsky <YvesGrabowsky@t-online.de>
Date: 06-05-99 13:03:13
Subject: @{b}Re: StormC & Hooks@{ub}

From: YvesGrabowsky@t-online.de (Yves Grabowsky)

Hello Stuart,

On 05-Jun-99 wrote Stuart Kelly (amigac@dkelly1.demon.co.uk):
> Hello All,
>          I have cereated a simple listview using MUI with
> my own construct & destruct hooks.  However when the
> destruct function is called the program crashes.
> 
> Am I decalring the hook functions wrong for StormC or is it
> another problem?
> 
> Any advice on this problem would be helpful.
> 

1) As far as I see there's no need to use SAVEDS and ASM macros in StromC,
because they are not supported.

2) If you just want a multi-column list, then you only need a display
hook, no construct and destruct hook. Remove these hooks, then you shouldn't
have any problems.

3) (only a suggestion) write your own header file, init, exit and fail
functions and don't use MUIs demo.h... (your program will get smaller and
you know what is what)

Cu,
-----------------------------------------------------------
Yves Grabowsky
