@NODE "Mail_362" " Re: Strange problem "
From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>
Date: 06-06-99 05:41:22
Subject: @{b}Re: Strange problem@{ub}

From: Ben Hutchings <womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk>

On Sat, Jun 05, 1999 at 10:28:22PM -0400, Bob Lanham wrote:
> From: Bob Lanham <BobL@leading.net>
> 
> 
> >    if(buffer=(UBYTE *)AllocVec(1024*768,MEMF_PUBLIC))
> 
> Isn't it supposed to go like this?:
> 
> if(buffer=AllocVec(1024*768*sizeof(UBYTE),MEMF_PUBLIC))

I think we can safely assume that sizeof(UBYTE) = 1.

I think the error is in the obvious place:

    WriteChunkyPixels(&(temp->RastPort),0,0,600,400,buffer,1024);

If you write to the screen's RastPort, the RastPort is not clipped, so
if the screen is smaller than 601 x 401 pixels this will write beyond
the screen boundaries.  Since this is a test program, I can forgive
that.  However, I suspect that Bob actually means to write 600 x 400
pixels and his Workbench screen is only 400 lines high.  So this is an
off-by-one error.

-----------------------------------------------------------
Ben Hutchings - womble@zzumbouk.demon.co.uk, http://nowhere.at.the.moment
Team *AMIGA* | Jay Miner Society | Linux - the choice of a GNU generation
