From: Linus McCabe <sparkle@hehe.com>

On 10-Jun-99, Ben Hutchings wrote:

> Either YAM or your configuration is broken.  It really should try to
> be a little cleverer about deciding whether such characters indicate
> emphasis.  It should also *never* delete the emphasis characters, just
> in case it gets this wrong.  That will screw up code like this and
> text that has to line up in columns.

I don't know how clever yam  is when it comes to this (not very, i dont
think), but it's easy to turn off the feature even temporarily by the
menuoption settings/textstyles, or amiga-t.

would be good if there was something like a standard <code> tag that  turned
off textstyles for a part of an email. (or maybe there is, but i just dont
know it)

/Linus
 
