@ENDNODE
@NODE "Mail_370" " Re: sub-structure dereferencing "
From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>
Date: 06-23-99 03:25:39
Subject: @{b}Re: sub-structure dereferencing@{ub}

From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>

On 22-Jun-99, ROBERT MEYERS wrote:

> The problem is how do I know which enclosing structure 
> the sub-structure which was processed belongs to?

Substract "offsetof(parent, sub)" from the pointer.
The offsetof-macro is defined in stddef.h

If you're using C++, then you could also just place your extra fields in a
subclass of C='s structure. Or for plain C, just place the sub-structure first,
since a pointer to a structure is also a pointer to the first member.

[...]
> I had some thoughts along the lines of comparing 
> addresses while walking through the Nodes in the List 
> that will hold the enclosing structure. e.g.,

Make it a balanced tree or use hashing to look up the structure, you should
never use a linear search when you have many items. But if I understand your
problem correct, you don't need to do any searching... :-)

Regards Allan
-----------------------------------------------------------
   Email: Duff@DIKU.DK
     URL: http://www.DIKU.dk/students/duff/


