@NODE "Mail_372" " Re: sub-structure dereferencing "
From: Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>
Date: 06-24-99 09:44:21
Subject: @{b}Re: sub-structure dereferencing@{ub}

From:    Rod Schnell <rodsch@telusplanet.net>

Hello ROBERT

On 22-Jun-99, ROBERT MEYERS wrote:

> Hardware passes the address of the sub-structure that it 
> was working on up to the software for housekeeping.
> 
> I had some thoughts along the lines of comparing 
> addresses while walking through the Nodes in the List 
> that will hold the enclosing structure. e.g.,

It'd be more efficient to put the enclosed struct as the first member after
the linkage node and use an offset from the address that is returned.

struct DaddyStruct
{
    struct Node linkage;
    struct BabyStruct baby;
    LONG somethingcritical;
    LONG somethingbad;
    LONG sonethingworse;
}dad;

When you get a *baby back, do something like this...

struct DaddyStruct *parent;

parent = baby - sizeof(struct Node);

  Rod


