@NODE "Mail_375" " Text file lines "
From: Mike Carter <mike.carter@bigfoot.com>
Date: 06-22-99 23:02:30
Subject: @{b}Text file lines@{ub}

From: "Mike Carter" <mike.carter@bigfoot.com>

Here's a real simple question (hopefully)...

What do people suggest to be the easiest way to read a line of text
(upto the NEWLINE \n character) into a string buffer using *only*
amiga run-time libraries?

FGets includes the NEWLINE so is not good.  But FGetC needs a loop so
is it the most efficent?  Would it be best to just use FGets and then
cut the last character off?

Comments appreciated please :)

Dinky do,


Mike C>

