@NODE "Mail_386" " Re: Text file lines "
From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>
Date: 06-28-99 00:31:02
Subject: @{b}Re: Text file lines@{ub}

From: Allan Odgaard <Duff@DIKU.DK>

On 27-Jun-99, Christian Hattemer wrote:

>> And if you ever release the program, you can count on it that someone will
>> edit the file by hand, removing a '\n' somewhere... Personally, I'd use
> I already released it, no complaints until now...
> If you need something to manage the Mailinglists you're subscribed to get
> ML-Support from Aminet.

Your program will not work correctly, if the user tampers with the saved data,
but you keep this in ascii, which is easily understood as an invitation to
alter entries manually ;-)
Maybe you should use IFF instead, especially as I believe your program is a MUI
program, which gives you many advantages in that direction, have a look at
MUI_DataSpace.Doc, MUIA_ObjectID, MUIM_Export and MUIM_Import, all three from
MUI_Notify.Doc.

>> asynicio functions, FGetsLenAsync() would be ideal for your purposes.
> Where do I find some Docs about it? I've searchd through all Autodocs but
> didn't find it.

AsyncIO.Doc assuming you've installed the developer files for asyncio.lib :-)

Regards Allan
