@NODE "Mail_400" " Re: titlebar (was example.c) "
From: Linus McCabe <sparkle@hehe.com>
Date: 06-12-99 07:09:41
Subject: @{b}Re: titlebar (was example.c)@{ub}

From: Linus McCabe <sparkle@hehe.com>

On 11-Jun-99, Felix Schwarz wrote:

> Is it possible to replace the titlebar of a window with a BOOPSI-gadget
> with the window-titlebar still remaining intact (e.g. for dragging, etc.)

I don't exactly understand what you want here. replace it but still leave
itintact. Anyway, you can make any boopsi gadget into a window dragbar by
adding the tag
 GA_SysGType,GTYP_WDRAGGING
so I guess you could replace the dragbar with a gadget like this and you
could still move around your window. 
Then how to deal with the other gadgets that normally overlap the titlebar,
I dont know. 

/Linus

