@NODE "Mail_401" " troubleshooting help "
From: jack york <jyork@voyager.net>
Date: 06-13-99 20:06:06
Subject: @{b}troubleshooting help@{ub}

From: jack york <jyork@voyager.net>

Hello,

I have a program that creates a process to handle the printing.  The 
child process can be sent any number of different reports to print.  No
matter which report I send, the program always fails like this:


10-Jun-99 09:16:18
Back wall was stomped upon
Data: 0000023A D100DEAD 00000001 0000023A 00000001 00000000 00000000
00000000
Addr: A000DEAD 0004B978 07AB2D1C 07AAF0DC 00000000 07AB2D0C 070007F8
078CE940
Stck: 00FA7F56 00000008 0000000D 07AAF11C 070039A4 00FA7FE6 07AB2D0C
071E392E
Stck: 07AAF11C 07AAF0DC 077ED0C8 07AB2D0C 070039A4 078CE9B0 070039A4
071F55A0
Name: "Shell Process"  CLI: "myprog" "ROM - graphics 40.24 (18.5.93)" Hunk
0000 Offset 0000432A
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
0x0004B978 = AllocMem(570,...)
Created on 10-Jun-99 09:15:54
        by task 0x077E0820
        at "ROM - graphics 40.24 (18.5.93)" Hunk 0000 Offset 00004284
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
16 byte(s) stomped (0x0004BBBC..0x0004BBCB), allocation+11 byte(s)
0004BBBC: E7......................DB....DB........ þ...........█..█....


The hunk (432A) is always the same even though that part of the code is
not used for some of the reports on which it fails. 

I am using Dice and ClassAct on a 3000.  I have the following debug
programs running:

  SegList
  Wipeout
  Enforcer
  Sashimi
  tnt

The flow of the child process is like this (only the essential parts
are being shown to save space):


WORD wbmain(struct WBStartup *wbs)
{
  OpenLibrary("requester.class", 0L);
  OpenLibrary("graphics.library", 36L);


  if (ButtonBase && WindowBase && LayoutBase && ...
  {               
      if ( CreateRecvPort()             //create port for messages
      {
         if (scr = LockPubScreen("MyScreen"))
         {
            APTR  visual_info;

            if ((visual_info = GetVisualInfo(scr, TAG_END)))
            {
               if (prt = MakeAllObjects())   //setup ClassAct window
               {
                 if (prt_window = CA_OpenWindow(prt))
                 {
                    UnlockPubScreen(NULL, scr);      
                    GetAttr(WINDOW_SigMask, prt, &winsig);

                    recv_sig   = 1L << p_recv_port->mp_SigBit;
               
                    while (! done)
                    {
                       wait = Wait( recv_sig | winsig);
                     
                       if (wait & recv_sig)
                       {
                          CopyMsg()
                          ReplyMsg((struct Message *)p_recv_msg);           
                    }

   
                       else if (wait & winsig)
                          HandleWindow()


Now, if I elimiate opening the window ( CA_OpenWindow ), everything
works fine.  I can run as many reports as I want and the program never 
fails.  I have tried removing the ClassAct code and just opening a 
standard intuition window and it still fails.  When I create the process
I have NP_StackSize, 100000.  It was only 8000 but I thought this might
be a stack problem and wanted to elimate that posibility.

I don't use AllocMem anywhere in the program (parent or child) so the
above failure seems to be a failure in the graphics module.  Or am I
making the module fail somehow?  How can I tell, if possible, what the
offset (4284 from above) into the graphics module points to?  Does 
anyone have any suggestions as to how I go about finding this problem?
I have tried everything I can think of.


Jack


