@NODE "Mail_403" " Re: troubleshooting help "
From: Jesper Svennevid <jesper@fxrealm.com>
Date: 06-14-99 15:02:56
Subject: @{b}Re: troubleshooting help@{ub}

From: "Jesper Svennevid" <jesper@fxrealm.com>



> > I see you call UnlockPubScreen(NULL, scr); immediately after opening the
> > window. You should retain the lock until you're finished using
> the screen,
> > all windows are closed and there's no chance of another one opening.
>
> I thought that the screen was locked while a window was opened on it?

Indeed, I think it's stated in the autodoc for LockPubScreen() (I can't
check ATM as I'm at work) that you don't need to keep the lock after
you've opened your window. If a program is trying to close the screen that
you have your window on, it'll wait until your window has been closed.

(That's why closing order is so important, as if you close your screen
before your window, your program will definatly lock up (been there, done
that :P))

--
// Jesper Svennevid




