@NODE "Mail_406" " variable args "
From: Duncan Strand <dstrand@zebs.screaming.net>
Date: 06-28-99 00:01:25
Subject: @{b}variable args@{ub}

From: Duncan Strand <dstrand@zebs.screaming.net>


I'm trying to write a function that does the same as sprintf, but
allocates memory for the resulting string.
So I could call the function like "str = newstr( "Cows %s %d times",
"moo", 3 );" and the string would contain "Cows moo 3 times"

I've looked through dices documenation and cannot find any reference to
variable argument functions.

The code below is as far as I've got. When run it displays "newstr =
"Cows x/P 2045182376 times""


#include <stdarg.h>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>

#include <exec/exec.h>

#include <clib/exec_protos.h>

char *newstr( STRPTR fmt, ... )
{
    va_list va;
    STRPTR dest = AllocVec( 5000, MEMF_CLEAR );   // The size is
temporary

    if( dest )
    {
        va_start( va, fmt );
        sprintf( dest, fmt, va );
        va_end( va );
    }
    return dest;
}

int main()
{
    char *str;

    str = newstr( "Cows %s %d times", "moo", 3 );

    printf( "newstr = \"%s\"\n", str );
    FreeVec( str );
    return 0;
}

-----------------------------------------------------------
-------------------------------------------------------------
Duncan Strand  ICQ: 16966914
