@NODE "Mail_409" " VBCC troubles "
From: Daithi O'Cuinn <docuinn@cluke.demon.co.uk>
Date: 06-12-99 22:54:58
Subject: @{b}VBCC troubles@{ub}

From: Daithi O'Cuinn <docuinn@cluke.demon.co.uk>

Hello,

i'm trying to compile a WarpOS program using VBCC. The program has no PPC
specific code, and compiles on 68k mode. However, when using the +warpos
switch, although it compiles okay, the linker gives an unreferenced symbols
error for every OS call, e.g.

Error 21: vc_1.o (.text+0x1254): Undefined reference to _SetRast.
Error 21: vc_1.o (.text+0x125c): Undefined reference to _RefreshWindowFrame.
Error 21: vc_1.o (.text+0x1e84): Undefined reference to _RefreshWindowFrame.

etc.

I can compile test programs for WarpOS, but not if they contain any OS calls.
Anyone know what I'm missing? Presumably some link library, but I don't know
enough about C compiler internals to track it down. I installed the whole 68k
and WOS VBCC archives.

Thanks,
-----------------------------------------------------------
Daithi O'Cuinn
docuinn@cluke.demon.co.uk


