@NODE "Mail_414" " Re: VBCC troubles "
From: Volker Barthelmann <volker@vb.franken.de>
Date: 06-14-99 00:13:30
Subject: @{b}Re: VBCC troubles@{ub}

From: Volker Barthelmann <volker@vb.franken.de>



On Sun, 13 Jun 1999, Daithi O'Cuinn wrote:

> I had a look at this - AFAICS it uses fd files to generate an amiga.lib, but I
> already have an amiga.lib in vbcc/machines/amigawos/lib

You may have to add "-lamiga" to link with amiga.lib.

> Anyone know why the compiler isn't accessing this properly?
> 
> The exact error is
> vlink -s -x -dn vlibm68k:startup.o "Ram Disk:Mountain.o" "Ram Disk:gui.o"  
> -lvc -lamiga -o mnt failed

This is not a linker line for warpos but for 68k. You have to add
"+warpos" when compiling as well as linking.

Volker


