Subject: @{b}WorkBench startup problems@{ub}

From: Tim Hanson <msinister@connectfree.co.uk>


    Hi All,
        I`ve just been trying to add WBench startup to my current project. (A
3D map editor.) Everything works fine until I try to save out a map. *This*
*works fine* from CLI but just crashes from WB. I`m using dice which handles
the WB startup by having a seperate function called int wbmain(struct
WBStartup *). I`m taking the arglist->names putting them in an array and
calling the normal main with them as argv. *This works fine* and it`ll load
the
file which has the map editor named as default tool. I can even load other
maps afterwards but as soon as I try to save: CRASH. No guru number just
blinking power light and good night. It`s hard to debug as the dice debugger
always runs things as CLI. 

    Is there something I should or shouldn`t do from a WB launched prog? or is
it my inept coding and things just being more sensitive for a WB launched
prog is showing up some mung I hadn`t noticed.

