Maybe - but I don't see the need for more than 2 lines.  Repetition
of the subject is particularly pointless!

Actually, what really irritates me is the way OneList essentially
repeats the From header line at the top of the body.  Does anyone know
why it does this?

<snip>
>     As to modifiying startup code the very thought brings me out in a cold
> sweat. Would you trust someone who declares a large array as a local variable
> (and doesn`t notice he`s done it) to start messing about in assembler. 

I wrote my own startup code for DICE which allowed me to make small
Amiga-specific programs.  It had a large number of optional features
so that it could be customised to the needs of each program.  I have
yet to do the same for gcc; libnix seems to have fairly good minimal
startup code anyway.

